The **Page **tab allows to configure the document page settings to be used during generation of the print spool.

> Note

*This section is displayed by default when accessing the Document Composition Project page.*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The available settings are:

**Setting**

**Description**

**Page formats**

Editable list of the available page formats.

Page formats set the width/height combination of the page and are assigned when creating master pages, as described in Layout View.

**Page attributes**

List of the available page attributes.

Page attributes can be used in the Output Configuration in the General Configuration Settings.

**Document states**

Document states identify the headers and footers of the entire shipment. Master pages are assigned to the headers and footers of the entire document.

## Page formats
This panel lists the available page formats and allows to create, edit or delete them.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Warning

*By default, new master pages are assigned the default ("Preset") format.*

*The default page format cannot be removed from the list, only modified.*

### Adding a page format
To add a new page format to the list, click ![](data:image/png;base64,).

Use the **in, cm **and **px **buttons to select the measurement unit to use for the height and width of the format.

### Deleting a page format
To delete a page format, select it and click  ![](data:image/png;base64,).

### Renaming a page format
To rename a page format, select it and enter the new name of the format in the first column.

### Setting the width and height of a page format
To set the width and height of the page, edit the values in the corresponding columns.

## Page attributes
This panel displays the attributes which can be assigned to the master pages; their value is correlated with the management of the output described in the General Configuration Settings.

> Warning

*It is not possible to add new attributes.*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Changing the name of an attribute
To rename an attribute, enter the new name in the corresponding text box.

## Document states
Document states identify the headers and footers of the entire shipment.

> Warning

*Master pages used in headers and footers can only host global contents.*

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Document state**

**Supported modes**

**Every page**

Foreground / Background

**Every page except the first**

Foreground / Background

**First page**

Foreground / Background

**Every page except the last**

Foreground

**Last page**

Foreground

**Cover**

Foreground

**Fill page**

Background
